  "texts": [
    "However, we observe that the adaptation of NLP techniques for dialects operates at several points in a typical NLP pipeline:(1) Training resources: Labeled datasets (including treebanks) and lexicons in dialects of a language have been reported in the past.",
    "This includes datasets with dialect labels along with additional task-specific labels, where the task is an NLP research problem.",
    "(2) Models: Models have been enhanced with several techniques, as may be typical of the time of the research.",
    "The fact that dialect-aware NLP can benefit from model adaptations and not dataset replacement alone is a key point of the survey.",
    "(3) Evaluation datasets: NLP techniques evaluated on datasets in dialects have peculiar observations."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}